The optical bandgap of P3DG was performed by UV–vis diffused reflection, and the converted plot of (αhυ)2 versus photon energy (hυ) was shown in Fig. 4
                        a. The transformation was calculated by the Tauc plot [21,22]. The bandgap value (Eg
                        ) was confirmed by measuring the intersection of baseline and tangent of the curve. Rich functional groups and numerous structure defects bring about a large bandgap of 4.76 eV. Ultraviolet photoelectron spectroscopy (UPS) was employed to inspect the work function (Φ) of P3DG, the corresponding spectrum is shown in Fig. 4b. The relation between all relevant parameters are shown in detail and the position of the Fermi level is considered at the binding energy of zero. The work function of P3DG is about 5.8 eV, determined by the equation of Φ = hυ – (Efermi - Ecutoff) [23]. Mott-Schottky analysis was further performed toward P3DG, which proves that P3DG is a p-type semiconductor (Fig. S2).
